<item>
            <title>[LU-8905] tests: sanity-hsm test_3[3-6] does not use ps correctly</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8905</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Tests 33 34 35 36 of sanity-hsm check that processes exit correctly (/ die when killed) using the following command:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;local there=$(ps -o pid,comm hp $pid &amp;gt;/dev/&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;)
[[ -z $there ]] || error &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Process&lt;/span&gt; dos not exit&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Obviously $there is always empty and the test is a noop. The output should not be redirected to /dev/null.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;test_33 fails when fixed, this is related to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5216&quot; title=&quot;HSM: restore doesn&amp;#39;t restart for new copytool&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-5216&quot;&gt;LU-5216&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
